Instructions for Updating as of Coursebuilder 1.8
-------------------------------------------------

0. Backup mobilecsp
1. Install lxml lib for Python (this was a major pain on the Mac)
   On MocOS, use $ STATIC_DEPS=true sudo pip install lxml
2. Download coursebuilder_1.8
3. Copy assets and data from mobilecsp  (optional, because we're downloading those)
   - 
4. Revise various files -- e.g., app.yaml, course_template.yaml, views/base.html, tools/verify.py
   -
5. Copy over modules and extensions for quizly

On App Engine
6. Download the data from mobilecsp to mobilecsp16-data.zip.
   $ sh scripts/etl.sh download course  /mobileCSP ram8647 ram8647.appspot.com --archive_path mobilecps-data.zip
7. Create a development server under my account :  elliptical-flow-95803.appspot.com
8. Update from the terminal with the v1.8 that you just created 
   $ appcfg.py update_indexes .
   $ appcfg.py update .
9. Upload the data from mobilecsp16-data.zip to elliptical-flow-95803
   See: https://developers.google.com/appengine/docs/python/tools/uploadinganapp#Python_Uploading_the_app
   $ sh scripts/etl.sh upload course /mobilecsp18 elliptical-flow-95803 elliptical-flow-95803.appspot.com --archive_path mobilecsp16-data.zip 
